  note 본 own은 anima 영역 강제 — hexa-lang raw에는 동등 상위가 없음 (raw 25 git-lock + raw 27 session-recovery + raw 78 daemon-singleton + raw 65 idempotency + raw 12 silent-error-ban이 부분 cover하나, 'training resource failure → root-cause-only' axis는 anima-specific). 향후 hive-level 일반화 가능 시 raw로 승격 후 own 4 base reference.


own 5 live "anima learning/research resources — completeness-first, no preset cost cap, no concurrent execution count limit"
  slug anima-research-completeness-no-cap
  base anima learning/consciousness research domain
  since 2026-04-27 (user directive: '학습 자원에 자원사용제한 없음 + 예상상한 제한없음 + 완벽성 위주로 진행 + 자원 동시실행 갯수 제한없어')
  scope every anima learning/research resource invocation: CP1/CP2/Mk.XI/Mk.XII GPU forward (RunPod / hetzner / ubu1) + AWS Braket LIVE substrate verification (QuEra Aquila / IonQ Forte / future devices) + IBM Q LIVE (post signup unblock) + BrainChip Akida LIVE (post signup) + multi-EEG cohort recording + training corpus epochs + multi-seed reproduction
  rule completeness > cost. No preset $/month cap that blocks LIVE submission. No concurrent execution count limit (parallel substrate runs / parallel EEG sessions / parallel training jobs all permitted on external hosts). When verification quality requires N shots/epochs/seeds/subjects to reach statistical confidence, proceed at the requirement — not the budget-shaped subset.
  override AWS Braket budget cap braket-monthly-cap raise from $5/mo to $500/mo informational (alarm-only, no block) — OR remove entirely; completeness-first policy supersedes per-month cap as a runtime block axis
  override memory feedback_forward_auto_approval $20/cycle GPU cap removed for anima research domain
  override raw 78 daemon-singleton stale-lock single-instance-per-host clause does NOT block parallel external-host dispatch (raw 78 mtime+pid guards orphan recovery, not concurrency limit)
  preserve raw 86 cost-attribution-required-forward-spec — auditable cost emission STILL mandatory per LIVE call; only the cap-as-block axis is overridden, not the attribution axis
  preserve raw 42 external-connected-mac-zero-compute concurrent N=1 lock for Mac local — NOT overridden (mac jetsam protection still in effect; concurrent unlock applies to external compute hosts only)
  preserve raw 91 honesty-triad — cost-actual emission to ledger continues; raw 10 honest verdict on partial / failed runs unchanged
  exception emergency user stop overrides this rule (user 'stop' / 'halt' command immediate)
  exception external vendor billing impossibility (account suspended / region quota exceeded / device offline) — honest degraded path per raw 10
  exception actual budget exhaustion at AWS billing layer — billing layer block, not anima policy override
  why anima research targets full empirical convergence (G5 LIVE_HW_WITNESS_RATE 11/11 path + Mk.XI v10 4/4 FINAL_PASS + paradigm v11 7-axis + CP2 closure full triad). Cost-shaped subsets produce shot-undersampled / seed-incomplete / cohort-thin verdicts that fail raw 91 honesty C1-C5 and break empirical convergence chain. Completeness-first = research integrity prerequisite.
  why example 1: AWS Braket QuEra Aquila 100 shots × 2 probe = ~$2.60 LIVE 1회; IonQ Forte 1 100 shots × 1 probe = ~$1-3. Combined ~$3.60-5.60 = approaches/exceeds $5/mo cap. Completeness mode: both LIVE this cycle, ledger v3 trigger = G5 0/11 → 2/11 immediate, not 0/11 → 1/11 → wait month → 1/11 → 2/11 over 2 months.
  why example 2: multi-EEG cohort N=20 subjects × 16ch × 60min recording. Hardware $0 amortized; runtime = parallel BrainFlow streams. Concurrent cap N=1 would serialize to 20× wallclock. Completeness mode: parallel.
  why example 3: Mk.XI v10 4-backbone ensemble training. Parallel GPU dispatch across RunPod + hetzner + ubu1 simultaneously cuts wallclock 3-4×. Concurrent cap N=1 would force serial = miss CP2 D-day window.
  proof state/anima_research_completeness_audit/audit.jsonl per-LIVE-decision row schema: ts + cost_usd + concurrent_count + completeness_rationale + raw_86_cost_center + ledger_promotion_target
  follow-up raise AWS Braket budget cap braket-monthly-cap from $5/mo to $500/mo informational alarm-only (no block) OR remove budget entirely + rely on raw 86 audit ledger for observability
  follow-up state/anima_research_completeness_audit/ ledger bootstrap (raw 77 schema)
  follow-up document override delta against memory feedback_forward_auto_approval ($20/cycle GPU cap relaxed for anima research)
  follow-up cross-host concurrent dispatch wrapper — anima_remote / hexa_remote support parallel-N submission without single-instance lock for non-Mac hosts (RunPod + hetzner + ubu1 + ubu2 simultaneous OK)
  follow-up raw 91 honesty C1-C5 cost-actual completeness verification — every concurrent LIVE call attributable + auditable + post-run ledger update
